  "response_text": "# High-Protein South Indian Dinner\n\nHere's a nutritious meal that fits your cuisine:\n\n## Main Dish\n**Sambar with Moong Dal or Chana Dal**\n- Protein-rich lentil base with vegetables\n- Naturally high in plant protein and fiber\n- Serve with rice or roti\n\n## Protein Boost Options\n- **Egg curry** (Muttai kulambu) - quick and protein-packed\n- **Fish curry** (if non-vegetarian) - excellent protein source\n- **Paneer fry or paneer curry** - vegetarian protein option\n\n## Accompaniments\n- **Rasam** - light, aids digestion\n- **Curd rice** or plain rice\n- **Stir-fried vegetables** (beans, carrots, leafy greens)\n- **Appalam or pickle** for flavor\n\n## Quick High-Protein Alternative\n**Dosa with sambhar + paneer filling**\n- Fermented batter provides protein\n- Add paneer or sprout filling for extra protein\n- Serve with chutney and sambhar\n\n## Tips\n- Use **chana dal, moong dal, or urad dal** liberally\n- Add **leafy greens** (spinach, fenugreek) to curries\n- Include **yogurt-based side dishes**\n- Consider **sprouted ingredients** for added nutrition\n\nThis approach keeps your traditional flavors while boosting protein content naturally.",
